        "text": "John 12:17-18",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " this demonstration is carefully traced to the raising of Lazarus: “the crowd which was with Him when He summoned Lazarus from the tomb, and raised him from the dead, testified [that He had done so], and on this account the crowd went out to meet Him, because they had heard this testimony”. The demonstration is thus rendered intelligible. In the Synoptists it is not accounted for. He is represented as entering the city with the pilgrims, and no reason is assigned for the sudden outburst of feeling. See ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
